      "description": "DRAM active tells us if we're memory-bandwidth bound (embedding models usually are at short seq and small batch, compute-bound at long seq / large batch). High `dram_active` with low `pipe_fp16_active` = HBM-bandwidth limited. PCIe RX+TX = host<->device transfer volume; should be small for an on-GPU inference loop.",
